Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.60,0:14:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Now, the more sophisticated person\Nwants to know, you know, what what does
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.12,0:14:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,ask yourself, what does mankind\Ngenerally
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.56,0:14:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,want to admit about itself and then\Nproject it onto others. So, the value of
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.12,0:14:48.63,Default,,0,0,0,,understanding the id is you see what\Npeople do not want to admit about
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.63,0:14:52.63,Default,,0,0,0,,themsel and they therefore project it\Nonto others.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.63,0:14:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So all the evil that they see everywhere\Nis generally a projection of their own
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.92,0:15:03.27,Default,,0,0,0,,hatred, hostilities, fears, jealousies\Netc.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.27,0:15:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So in psychoanalysis you become familiar\Nwith the id. The id is all that is
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.16,0:15:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,forbidden and repressed.\NOne of the deepest things hidden is the
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.92,0:15:21.72,Default,,0,0,0,,death instinct.\NDeath instinct.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.92,0:15:27.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The desire to kill.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.19,0:15:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Thank you.\N>> Freud said there's aeros and thantos.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.00,0:15:44.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Aeros is the basic instinct of life and\Nlove. Thanoos is the basic attraction of
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.32,0:15:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,death.\NAnd certainly at the guillanti
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.80,0:15:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,guillotine 15,000 died in the guillotine\Nand throngs by the hundreds of thousands
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.24,0:16:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,witnessed the event\Ntheir death instinct. Yeah. Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.56,0:16:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Hello. Um, I listen to you discussing\Nprayer and I pray morning and evening
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.88,0:16:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and sometimes in between and I always\Nask the Lord, may I be a servant of the
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.56,0:16:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Lord as part of that? And when I do that\Nevery morning,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.24,0:16:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,>> put yourself close to the mic. See if I\Ncan hear you better.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.72,0:16:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Okay.\N>> Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.92,0:16:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,>> I've I've asked to be a servant of the\NLord.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.88,0:16:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yes. So anything that shows up in my\Nworld that day is mine for some reason
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.00,0:16:38.72,Default,,0,0,0,,>> because I I have asked for it.\N>> Yes. Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.72,0:16:46.24,Default,,0,0,0,,>> So if I've got um a tremendous amount of\Npain like physical pain and it's not
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.24,0:16:54.07,Default,,0,0,0,,gone away with say treatment or I've\Ntried to disappear it according to your
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.07,0:17:01.27,Default,,0,0,0,,tapes. So would I be right in assuming\Nthat this is karmic and possibly I've
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.27,0:17:08.79,Default,,0,0,0,,caused pain to others and this is I\N>> I have pain and I just pray to forgive
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.79,0:17:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,myself to have forgiveness for having\Ncaused pain to others and just suffer it
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.40,0:17:20.79,Default,,0,0,0,,like just I have to live like the pain\Njust has to be felt. Is is that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.79,0:17:25.03,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Not necessarily but it is an option at\None time.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.03,0:17:31.36,Default,,0,0,0,,uh later on you can let go experiencing\Nthe pain itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.36,0:17:35.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh if you quit resisting it eventually\Nit will run out.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.84,0:17:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Pain will only last so long. So\Nif you quit resisting it and eventually
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.52,0:17:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,it runs out. When you've run out that\Nyou know Es used to call it a stack when
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.84,0:17:52.08,Default,,0,0,0,,when that stack has run out it's run\Nout. Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.08,0:17:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Okay. So uh but a certain what I was\Nwondering is like what I said to myself
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.36,0:18:05.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and as part of my prayer since it hasn't\Ngone in other ways that for some reason
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.03,0:18:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I do have to experience it.\N>> Well then you weren't praying if you're
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.84,0:18:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,willing to resist it.\NYou're questioning it, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.00,0:18:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yes.\N>> First you ask for it, then you question
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.64,0:18:18.64,Default,,0,0,0,,it and don't want it when you get it,\Nright?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.64,0:18:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yes. Yeah. I\NI think I think I've got the answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.00,0:18:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,>> You got it. Okay.\N>> Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.55,0:18:31.12,Default,,0,0,0,,>> It'll go away.\N>> It'll go away.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.12,0:18:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yeah.\N>> It'll either go away or your awareness
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.52,0:18:39.52,Default,,0,0,0,,of it will disappear.\NIt'll still be there if you think about
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.52,0:18:45.67,Default,,0,0,0,,it, but you never think about it. So,\N>> hi. Um,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.67,0:18:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,in working with young children like age\Nsix or seven, what would you say are the
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.96,0:18:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,top one or two spiritual practices that\Nare important for supporting them?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.76,0:19:00.08,Default,,0,0,0,,>> I can't understand.\N>> She's working with children that are
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.08,0:19:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,like six and seven age group six and\Nseven. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.28,0:19:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,>> What would you say is their top uh\Npractices that you would advise to them
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.76,0:19:12.79,Default,,0,0,0,,to use\N>> the children to use? Because you said
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.79,0:19:15.84,Default,,0,0,0,,the link to happiness.\N>> Yeah. The
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.84,0:19:19.03,Default,,0,0,0,,>> remember the first slides he did on the\Nlink between happiness
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.03,0:19:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,>> between happiness\N>> and joy and
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.44,0:19:23.12,Default,,0,0,0,,>> joy\N>> to get them up to those states.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.12,0:19:26.16,Default,,0,0,0,,>> To get them up to those states.\N>> Six-year-olds you don't have to worry
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.16,0:19:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,about. They're already in that all the\Ntime.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.00,0:19:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,>> I guess I guess supporting them to stay\Nin that. I guess trying to do some some
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.00,0:19:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,things to help. If you develop the\Ncapacity to be loving and concerned
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.40,0:19:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,about others, loving concerned about\Nothers, also loving towards yourself and
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.96,0:19:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,loving towards your parents, loving\Ntowards your classmates.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.08,0:19:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,That's probably the most advanced thing\Nyou can learn, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.28,0:19:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,>> kindness.\N>> Kindness. Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.88,0:19:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yeah. Children can be nasty.\N>> They could be really the worst,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.76,0:19:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,>> especially to each other.\N>> Yep.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.40,0:20:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,>> So, I would teach him kindness out of\Nanything else and compassion. Well, you
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.72,0:20:07.20,Default,,0,0,0,,can start with animals, kindness to\Ndoggies and kitties and that which is,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.20,0:20:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, going to protect itself,\N>> compassion for all living things. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.64,0:20:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,>> And the willingness to help each other.\N>> Friendliness. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.28,0:20:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Friendliness and willing to, you know,\Nif someone if a child falls down, go
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.00,0:20:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,over and see if they need help or, you\Nknow, help them up. So, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.24,0:20:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,six-year-olds, if you teach that at that\Nage, I think that that makes them better
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.00,0:20:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,human beings in the long run. That's\Nkindergarten, first grade, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.60,0:20:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Thank you.\N>> Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.00,0:20:51.84,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Better you than me.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.84,0:20:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Hello, Dr. Hawkins. Hello, Susan.\N>> Um, okay. So, my question has to do with
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.32,0:21:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the moment of death. with the mode of\Ndeath.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.36,0:21:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,>> The moment\N>> moment of death. Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.40,0:21:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,>> And um I guess it's a fear of that I'll\Ngo to sleep and I and
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.55,0:21:16.08,Default,,0,0,0,,wanting to stay awake, you know, when I\Ndie. If that makes
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.08,0:21:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,>> No, you won't want to stay awake.\N>> I won't.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.28,0:21:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,>> What would you want to hang on to that\Nfor?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.52,0:21:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,>> I had a Okay. I had a Buddhist teacher\Nbefore who said that if you don't stay
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.60,0:21:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,awake\Nwhen you're dying that you'll end up
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.28,0:21:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,back on the karmic wheel. Um, does that\Nthat doesn't make any sense?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.32,0:21:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Oh, I know what you're saying. Yes. If\Nyou're not aware that you're dying and
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.40,0:21:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and you go on living not knowing that\Nyou're dead,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.20,0:21:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,>> that is a problem. Yeah.\N>> So, can you call out for help from
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.32,0:21:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,somebody like you at a time like that?\NUm
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.48,0:21:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,>> you can choose to remain conscious\Nthrough the transition
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.64,0:22:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,first of all by knowing that death is\Nnot a possibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.36,0:22:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The only thing can happen is you leave\Nthe body. But you're right a lot of
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.76,0:22:09.91,Default,,0,0,0,,people believe in death is such an\Nextreme you know amount that they'll
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.91,0:22:15.08,Default,,0,0,0,,sometimes go unconscious for a couple\Nhundred years.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.67,0:22:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,,>> So you can choose to stay conscious.\N>> You can choose to stay conscious.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.08,0:22:23.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You ask God to be with you. And don't\Nforget you have helper angels. You ask
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.52,0:22:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,your gu your guiding angels to help you\Nstay conscious and to learn from this
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.96,0:22:32.79,Default,,0,0,0,,experience through this transition. Yes.\N>> Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.79,0:22:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,>> And when you die, you're not going to\Nreally care about it at all because the
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.88,0:22:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,body is laying there, but you're not the\Nbody. So, it's rather irrelevant what
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.60,0:22:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,what's happening to the body. In fact,\Nthe body is extremely boring.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.76,0:22:49.91,Default,,0,0,0,,>> It's a dumbl looking thing. The idea\Nthat you ever cherished it to such a
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.91,0:22:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,degree seems like an absurdity.\N>> Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.40,0:22:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,>> It's really a dumb looking thing laying\Nthere.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.88,0:23:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,There any desire to get back in at day\Ntruth. If you're karmically decent that
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.36,0:23:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,you have to go back, you do. But it\Nisn't,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.52,0:23:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, you think, well, you would\Nhave an aversion to leaving the body and
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.72,0:23:14.15,Default,,0,0,0,,physical death. On the contrary,\N>> okay,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.15,0:23:20.44,Default,,0,0,0,,>> on the contrary.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.55,0:23:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yeah.\N>> Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.60,0:23:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Hi.\N>> Um I have a I guess a psychoanalyst
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.72,0:23:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,question. um if when going through the\Nprocess of um you know working with a
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.40,0:23:44.15,Default,,0,0,0,,therapist, they ask you to uh drag up\Nyour childhood memories and and try to
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.15,0:23:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,um unear things that are causing pain\Nand I just want to ask your uh advice is
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.76,0:23:52.24,Default,,0,0,0,,what's the best way to deal with that?\NIs it
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.24,0:23:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,>> does a therapist actually ask you to do\Nthat? Uh it's actually a family member
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.24,0:24:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,of mine and they have Yes.\N>> Usually well in psychoanalysis you you
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.44,0:24:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,report anything and everything that\Ncomes to your mind as it arises. You
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.48,0:24:11.20,Default,,0,0,0,,don't try to categorize it. This is\Nchildhood. This is adolescence.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.20,0:24:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,This is more like a scholarly\N>> okay
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.32,0:24:19.20,Default,,0,0,0,,>> examination of yourself. But that could\Nbe a place to start a scholarly
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.20,0:24:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,examination of what your childhood was\Nlike etc. Mhm.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.64,0:24:26.72,Default,,0,0,0,,>> And that of course will bring up\Nassociated memories and feelings
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.72,0:24:31.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's the associated\Ninterpretation and feelings that you
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.27,0:24:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,know you work with in therapy.\N>> Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.84,0:24:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,>> The fact that you were born and\Ngraduated from kindergarten at age five
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.36,0:24:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,is just immaterial you know.\N>> Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.60,0:24:44.15,Default,,0,0,0,,>> But the events that happened there and\Nthe emotions that were left with that
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.15,0:24:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,you try to see a connection between\Nthose things and the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.60,0:24:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Okay.\NAnd is it if you have like a like let's
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.00,0:24:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,say you had an abusive parent, right?\NIs it enough to just experience it or is
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.52,0:25:02.08,Default,,0,0,0,,there a tool like um and the family\Nmember I'm that I'm talking to or I'm
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.08,0:25:05.44,Default,,0,0,0,,asking about is having a lot of trouble\Nforgiving that they had an abusive
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.44,0:25:11.67,Default,,0,0,0,,mother. Um is there a tool that is is it\Njust to you know the the therapist has
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.67,0:25:15.03,Default,,0,0,0,,asked them just to bring it up right and\Njust to experience it and experience it
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.03,0:25:19.91,Default,,0,0,0,,like a victim like as a child. Is that\Nenough or is this should we seek help
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.91,0:25:23.27,Default,,0,0,0,,elsewhere? I guess is a\N>> well you you you bring it up and see the
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.27,0:25:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,conclusions that you drew about yourself\Nand about life etc. And you you try and
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.00,0:25:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,compare that to a more sophisticated\Nadult view.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.44,0:25:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Okay.\N>> And to like so it's more like
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.60,0:25:40.64,Default,,0,0,0,,re-education more like re-education\Nbut it may take some some working
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.64,0:25:45.36,Default,,0,0,0,,through to re-educate yourself.\N>> Okay. that to make make a mistake
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.36,0:25:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't mean that you're worthless and\Nhave to go hide in the closet and kill
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.64,0:25:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,yourself.\N>> Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.48,0:25:59.03,Default,,0,0,0,,>> That it's okay. So a more permissive\Nsuper ego. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.03,0:26:03.52,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Okay. Thank you.\N>> It's not necessary to take such an
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.52,0:26:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,extreme\Nself-punitive view of mistakes and
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.44,0:26:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,errors.\NSo you become more congenial toward
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.48,0:26:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,yourself.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.40,0:26:20.12,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Thank you.\N>> Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.76,0:26:30.79,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yes.\N>> Thank you so much. Could you explain um
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.79,0:26:36.79,Default,,0,0,0,,the difference between compassion\Ntowards someone and enabling so that I
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.79,0:26:42.79,Default,,0,0,0,,can make sure that I'm not getting in\Nthe way of someone's karmic
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.79,0:26:45.67,Default,,0,0,0,,undoing?\N>> Compassion means accepting that that's
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.67,0:26:52.12,Default,,0,0,0,,part of the human potential.\NAnd um
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.64,0:26:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and compared to what was the compared to\Nwhat?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.44,0:26:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Enabling.\N>> Enabling. Oh, enabling. Well, enabling
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.96,0:27:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,means to assist the other person in that\Nbehavior, to assist, to contribute to
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.00,0:27:09.60,Default,,0,0,0,,it. If they're problem is they're\Nfeeling sorry for themsel, an enabler
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.60,0:27:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,would say, "Oh, poor so- and so. Oh, you\Ndid have a terrible time and you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.88,0:27:18.32,Default,,0,0,0,,potentiated\Ninstead of trying to get the person to
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.32,0:27:22.72,Default,,0,0,0,,see that that's that was happened at\Nthat time for what could be learned from
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.72,0:27:27.03,Default,,0,0,0,,it at that time, but now is a different\Ntime." And therefore we have to grow
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.03,0:27:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,beyond these things. Enabling means you\Nassist the person with excuses for to
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.64,0:27:38.24,Default,,0,0,0,,continue pathologic behavior.\NYou know the classic example is the
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.24,0:27:44.79,Default,,0,0,0,,alcoholic whose spouse you know makes\Nexcuses for him etc. So the take
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.79,0:27:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,responsibilities.\NSo it' be a matter of taking
